President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Brad R. Carson is nominated for Under Secretary of the Army, Maureen Elizabeth Cormack is nominated for Ambassador to Bosnia and Herzegovina, Leslie Berger Kiernan is nominated for Representative of the United States to the United Nations for U.N. Management and Reform, David Radzanowski is nominated for Chief Financial Officer of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA), and John Roth is nominated for Inspector General of the Department of Homeland Security. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Anita K. Blanchard, Gargee Ghosh, and John D. Podesta to key Administration posts. Additionally, President Obama appointed Alan J. Patricof to a key Administration post.